<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2413/136–137.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Chinese
                                Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-29"><hi rend="italic">May 29,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 113.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith copy
                            of an act of Congress, approved May 25, 1908,<note n="1" xml:id="d55fn1">Supra.</note> whereby the President is authorized to return to the
                            Chinese Government a designated portion of the <pb facs="0168" n="66" xml:id="pg_66"/> indemnity paid by your Government in consideration
                            of losses sustained by reason of the Boxer disturbances of 1900.</p>
                        <p>The Government of the United States would be glad to obtain from the
                            Imperial Chinese Government an expression of opinion as to the times and
                            manner in which the remission shall be made.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>